; Inline cost amounts should set the price commodity's display precision
; so that auto-balanced amounts render correctly and balance assertions
; detect mismatches.  Previously, `@ $1.03` left the $ commodity at
; precision 0, causing $-10.30 to display as $-10 and balance assertions
; against $-10.00 to incorrectly pass.

2015/12/15
    Assets:Stock                10 AAPL @  $1.03
    Assets:Checking

test bal Assets:Checking
             $-10.30  Assets:Checking
end test

test bal Assets:Stock
             10 AAPL  Assets:Stock
end test

; Balance assertion against the correct amount should succeed.
2015/12/16
    [Assets:Checking]           $0  = $-10.30

test bal Assets:Checking
             $-10.30  Assets:Checking
end test
